Instructions for making a new release:

1) git checkout master
2) git clean -d -x -f         # I hope you've commit or stashed everything
                              # you are working on
2) git fetch
3) git rebase origin
4) ./autogen.sh && ./configure
5) make bumpver
6) git commit -a
7) git clean -d -x -f
8) ./autogen.sh && ./configure
9) make release

If packaging in RPM format, you might find the 'make rpmlog' target useful.
It gives you an RPM spec file formatted changelog block that contains the
git shortlog entries of all changes since the last tag.

Resulting pyparted-X.Y.tar.gz is the release.  'cp -a' this to the pkg
CVS tree and make a new build.  Also need to copy it to the project
download site and make a new version entry in the Trac site.

10) git push
11) git push --tags
12) Edit configure.ac and change the version from X.Y to X.(Y+1)-devel
13) git add configure.ac
14) git commit
15) git push
